    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_319174">Hey all, just started getting into this with friends, and I have to say, I'm mostly pleased. SR was never the simplest game to pick up and play, and that hasn't really changed, however the rules system has been overhauled so that it was a sort of &quot;one size fits all&quot; method of game play. Everything is opposed tests, with Attribute + Skill, with everyone using the same target numbers, period. <br />
<br />
There are some down sides though. I think magic is wtf over powered now. Non-casters use only one dice pool to resist spells, and stuff like mana or power bolt doesn't even need to hit. In our last session, I watched one of our power gamers make a Wolf Shaman out of the box, no special favors granted, who could summon like 3-6 rated wolf Spirits and laugh the drain off. If he wanted to, he could have summoned a 12 rated Wolf Spirit and only taken some very minor drain. Was pretty annoying, we walk into the Stuffer Shack, and some guys try to rob the place. Two turns later, every single one of them is running in terror from the guy's wolf spirits, while 3 other Shadowrunners just sort of stand around with their thumbs up their asses. Not to mention that his initiative rolls for himself and his wolves go a little something like this: 18, 20, 22. My decker managed to get the next highest initiative at 12. <br />
<br />
Something is totally ****** with the costs of Fetishes and Foci. He achieved such a high init with a sustaining focus running an uber speed spell, and all his other 5 foci helped him summon like nobodies business. Oh, AND he and his wolf spirits all get 3 initiative passes, because spirits are nasty and he paid a few measly character creation build points to buy foci, that if bought during game, would cost him an arm and leg in both karma and the amount of time and energy he'd have to invest. The Foci allows him to maintain an unbelievably powerful initiative spell for no drain, that he doesn't have to maintain in any sort of wy. At charcter creation, all it takes is some decent Nuyen (which equals the cost of one of my mid to upper range decking programs, which don't do **** for me compared to foci) and a very low BP investment. (I think like 5 BP, maybe?)<br />
<br />
Anyways, I think it's pretty good but its got some big ass holes in the rules system. Anyone else have any thoughts?</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
