<br />
<div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">The problem I am seeing here is that a caster with a high magic and sorcery rating can cast low force spells that aren't any easier to resist by the target, but whose drain is laughably easy to resist. Add in a good powerfocus and the mage is going to be nasty. And it would be relatively easy this mage to cast 2 or 3 spells at once, still taking no drain.</div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>This was the exact same conclusion the problem player came to prior to game as he deconstructed the magic system for us. The inability of mundanes to resist even weak magic with consistency makes mages uber against anything but the decked out kill squad.</div>
